commitResults.messageTitle: Added functionality to view events that occurred at a given date
commitResults.messageBody:
Parser class is now able to parse a given input string and match it with valid events that occurred on that day.

Also did general improvements for javadocs
When the user types in the word "help" into the chatbot, a google document containing all the appropriate commands and syntax will appear

Small bugfixing before merging with main
Changed the main background color of JavaFX
Improved parser logic to parse the first input command

JavaDoc methods are too short and undescriptive

The parameter tags are often missing or one-liners at best.

Other users reading the code might not have sufficient idea as to what is going on with the code.

Let's update the JavaDocs in line with recommendations from the textbook.

As well as checkstyle to provide more description, even in helper methods.

Doing so allows readers to understand the codebase better at a glance
Update some method names to verb form

Reduced redundant code for index related tasks

More informative error calls for "help" function

commitResults.messageTitle: Change naming conventions in Parser.java and Storage.java
commitResults.messageBody:
Parser and Storage classes contain a lot of low-level functionalities

Intermediary variables are currently named inappropriately

Providing better naming conventions improves the overall readability

And removing magic numbers gives meaning to constants throughout the codebase

Let's refactor the naming scheme for the low-level classes

Into names that are better appreciated by developers
And provide some meaning to the variable's purpose and type
